cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.AI 

This paper is related to wireless communication systems and vehicular networks, which are typically categorized under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses resource allocation and optimization, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper addresses reliability and security concerns, which are relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the use of a mobility model and optimization algorithm suggests a potential connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well.
